laboratory_examinations.findings: Documents multiple episodes of NSVT lasting 26 beats and records 4665 premature ventricular contractions.
Demonstrates normal sinus rhythm, incomplete right bundle branch block, and multiple T-wave abnormalities.

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Complete blood cell count, electrolyte, renal function, and thyroid function testing

laboratory_examinations.findings: Shows normal left ventricular function and chamber size, normal right ventricular function, upper limits of normal size, and no valvular or pericardial abnormalities.
Reveals normal coronary arteries and a normal left ventricular ejection fraction of >65%.

Shows borderline dilated left ventricle with normal LV mass and systolic function, right ventricle dilated with normal global systolic function, distal one-third of the right ventricle akinetic, and subendocardial delayed enhancement of the distal one-third of the right ventricle.
